Remissio: The allusion is to the annus remissionis (Ezech. 46, 17), or Year of Jubilee, which in the Old Law occurred every fifty years (ef. Lev. 25). During the Year of Jubilee, debts were remitted, slaves liberated‚ etc. Read the article on Jubilee, in the ³ Cath. Eneyol.
